1
00:01:25,700 --> 00:01:34,900
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

2
00:01:35,390 --> 00:01:37,870
[Episode 23]

3
00:01:43,670 --> 00:01:45,390
[Notice of participation
in the National Singer Competition]

4
00:01:47,180 --> 00:01:48,370
Right face!

5
00:01:48,840 --> 00:01:49,450
Rise!

6
00:01:49,580 --> 00:01:54,770
[Congratulations to Zhuang Zhuang for making it
to the finals of the Singer Competition]

7
00:01:54,810 --> 00:01:57,009
[Notice of participation
in the National Singer Competition]

8
00:01:57,110 --> 00:02:03,070
[Congratulations to Zhuang Zhuang for making it
to the finals of the Singer Competition]

9
00:02:05,330 --> 00:02:06,780
[Congratulations to Zhuang Zhuang for making it
to the finals of the Singer Competition]

10
00:02:09,750 --> 00:02:13,130
Welcome! Welcome!

11
00:02:13,310 --> 00:02:16,840
Welcome! Welcome!

12
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:17,500
Have a seat!

13
00:02:19,650 --> 00:02:20,510
Zhuang Zhuang!

14
00:02:20,780 --> 00:02:22,710
Congratulations
on making it to the finals.

15
00:02:22,710 --> 00:02:23,579
All of us

16
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:25,090
hope you achieve

17
00:02:25,310 --> 00:02:26,910
great results in the finals.

18
00:02:27,300 --> 00:02:30,820
Congratulations! Congratulations!

19
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:34,340
Congratulations! Congratulations!

20
00:02:34,500 --> 00:02:35,210
Zhuang Zhuang

21
00:02:35,210 --> 00:02:36,360
will definitely win first place

22
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:37,579
and become the champion.

23
00:02:37,579 --> 00:02:40,820
Zhuang Zhuang is the champion!

24
00:02:40,960 --> 00:02:44,290
Zhuang Zhuang is the champion!

25
00:02:44,579 --> 00:02:45,030
We were planning

26
00:02:45,030 --> 00:02:46,420
to eat out,

27
00:02:46,579 --> 00:02:47,310
but everyone felt

28
00:02:47,310 --> 00:02:49,370
it was better to stay in—
more comfortable.

29
00:02:49,370 --> 00:02:49,780
Yes.

30
00:02:50,079 --> 00:02:51,380
If we get drunk,

31
00:02:51,410 --> 00:02:53,070
we can just go to bed and sleep.

32
00:02:53,180 --> 00:02:53,620
Right?

33
00:02:53,650 --> 00:02:54,360
Xu said

34
00:02:54,410 --> 00:02:55,680
this meal today

35
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:56,810
should show our sincerity,

36
00:02:56,810 --> 00:02:58,510
so each of us cooked a dish

37
00:02:58,650 --> 00:02:59,850
to make a full spread.

38
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:03,100
Zhuang, we also prepared a performance.

39
00:03:03,690 --> 00:03:05,250
Cao prepared the performance.

40
00:03:05,250 --> 00:03:06,160
Introduce it.

41
00:03:06,430 --> 00:03:09,310
Zhuang Zhuang,
the fact that you made it to the finals

42
00:03:09,310 --> 00:03:10,440
really inspired us.

43
00:03:10,580 --> 00:03:11,000
You are

44
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:12,300
the pride of our Seasons Change Hostel.

45
00:03:12,300 --> 00:03:12,960
You've warmed us

46
00:03:12,960 --> 00:03:13,890
and inspired us.

47
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:15,210
You're not alone in this competition.

48
00:03:15,210 --> 00:03:16,520
You carry our dreams too.

49
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:18,910
Yes, we all have to shine.

50
00:03:21,180 --> 00:03:24,120
Ready—

51
00:03:26,740 --> 00:03:29,620
Seven-character poem: The Long March.

52
00:03:30,340 --> 00:03:33,530
The Red Army fears not the Long March.

53
00:03:34,130 --> 00:03:37,280
Countless rivers and mountains
are but trivial.

54
00:03:38,020 --> 00:03:42,060
The Five Ridges rise in gentle waves.

55
00:03:42,579 --> 00:03:46,740
The grandeur of the Wumeng Mountains is nothing
more than clay balls rolling beneath our feet.

56
00:03:46,740 --> 00:03:49,840
The Jinsha River
warms the cliffs with splashes.

57
00:03:50,210 --> 00:03:54,310
The Dadu Bridge
chills with its iron chains.

58
00:03:54,620 --> 00:03:58,400
We rejoice in the snow
across the Min Mountains.

59
00:03:58,840 --> 00:04:03,180
After the three armies have crossed,
everyone's faces are beaming.

60
00:04:10,180 --> 00:04:10,840
Why are you crying?

61
00:04:10,840 --> 00:04:11,660
Look at you.

62
00:04:12,020 --> 00:04:13,020
What are you doing?

63
00:04:13,020 --> 00:04:13,880
Sit, sit.

64
00:04:14,530 --> 00:04:15,240
Sit.

65
00:04:15,370 --> 00:04:17,070
Come on, let's drink.

66
00:04:17,810 --> 00:04:19,010
Eat up.

67
00:04:19,100 --> 00:04:19,950
That was too much, wasn't it?

68
00:04:19,950 --> 00:04:20,410
Come on.

69
00:04:20,430 --> 00:04:21,829
Well, we wanted to make her happy.

70
00:04:21,829 --> 00:04:22,800
-Come on.
-To make her happy.

71
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:23,930
She is. She is happy.

72
00:04:23,930 --> 00:04:24,600
Tears of joy.

73
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:25,060
Come on.

74
00:04:27,810 --> 00:04:29,010
Come on, let's drink.

75
00:04:29,370 --> 00:04:31,300
Why do you need so much money again?

76
00:04:31,430 --> 00:04:33,230
Didn't I just transfer it to you?

77
00:04:34,770 --> 00:04:36,970
You know so many bosses.

78
00:04:37,070 --> 00:04:38,710
You can borrow from them.

79
00:04:39,390 --> 00:04:40,890
What bosses do I know?

80
00:04:42,330 --> 00:04:44,390
The one who came to our house last time.

81
00:04:44,390 --> 00:04:45,800
He's been to our home.

82
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:47,670
Why can't you borrow from him?

83
00:04:47,830 --> 00:04:49,159
Come on. What does his richness

84
00:04:49,159 --> 00:04:50,330
have to do with me?

85
00:04:50,390 --> 00:04:51,130
Besides, why is Fufu

86
00:04:51,130 --> 00:04:52,960
in such a hurry to get married?

87
00:04:53,100 --> 00:04:55,590
But we need to prepare in advance.

88
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:58,380
I'm living in a basement, Mom.

89
00:05:00,220 --> 00:05:01,670
What do you mean, Ranran?

90
00:05:01,830 --> 00:05:02,360
Do you

91
00:05:02,370 --> 00:05:04,030
not want to help your brother?

92
00:05:04,630 --> 00:05:06,100
Let me make it clear.

93
00:05:06,220 --> 00:05:07,480
All our family's money

94
00:05:07,500 --> 00:05:09,360
was spent on your acting classes.

95
00:05:09,360 --> 00:05:11,540
You have to contribute to the family.

96
00:05:11,870 --> 00:05:13,370
If you feel awkward

97
00:05:13,370 --> 00:05:14,690
borrowing money from those bosses,

98
00:05:14,690 --> 00:05:15,950
I can call

99
00:05:15,980 --> 00:05:16,840
Mr. Chu myself.

100
00:05:16,980 --> 00:05:17,950
Please don't.

101
00:05:19,930 --> 00:05:21,460
I got it. I'll figure it out.

102
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:23,060
Okay, I'll wait for you.

103
00:05:33,050 --> 00:05:34,940
[Seasons Change Hostel]

104
00:05:40,220 --> 00:05:41,659
Zongbao, what are you doing?

105
00:05:41,659 --> 00:05:43,110
I finally got some sleep.

106
00:05:48,270 --> 00:05:49,870
Zongbao, what are you doing?

107
00:05:49,870 --> 00:05:50,870
I finally got to catch up on sleep,

108
00:05:50,870 --> 00:05:52,409
and you're doing renovations here?

109
00:05:52,409 --> 00:05:53,730
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

110
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:55,720
I got a new gadget here.

111
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:56,830
I was just trying it out.

112
00:05:56,830 --> 00:05:58,120
Come on. You...

113
00:05:58,390 --> 00:05:59,600
Not only are you mashing garlic here,

114
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:00,740
you're also making a sound
like a power drill.

115
00:06:00,740 --> 00:06:01,800
What are you trying to do?

116
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:02,460
I really...

117
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:03,020
Come on.

118
00:06:03,770 --> 00:06:05,510
The garlic mashed by hand

119
00:06:03,810 --> 00:06:09,100
[Endeavor]

120
00:06:05,930 --> 00:06:07,450
tastes different from the garlic paste

121
00:06:07,450 --> 00:06:08,560
made by a machine.

122
00:06:09,830 --> 00:06:10,600
How is it different?

123
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:11,660
What is that thing?

124
00:06:11,730 --> 00:06:14,670
[Endeavor]

125
00:06:12,130 --> 00:06:14,430
This is a juicer.

126
00:06:14,720 --> 00:06:15,360
Sir, sir.

127
00:06:15,480 --> 00:06:15,810
What?

128
00:06:15,830 --> 00:06:16,290
Well...

129
00:06:16,510 --> 00:06:17,600
You worked hard on the performance.

130
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:19,060
Let's eat and drink together.

131
00:06:19,060 --> 00:06:19,620
I shouldn't.

132
00:06:19,620 --> 00:06:21,450
I have a performance, so I can't drink.

133
00:06:21,450 --> 00:06:22,680
Don't just drink water.

134
00:06:22,680 --> 00:06:24,080
Here, try this beverage.

135
00:06:24,120 --> 00:06:25,360
It's yam juice produced

136
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:26,000
in our village.

137
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:26,660
Have a taste.

138
00:06:26,660 --> 00:06:28,060
Have a taste and see how it is.

139
00:06:28,060 --> 00:06:30,270
You can make juice out of yams?

140
00:06:30,330 --> 00:06:32,290
Yes, it's very nutritious.

141
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:33,400
Is that so?

142
00:06:35,240 --> 00:06:36,370
Refreshing, right?

143
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:37,920
And it's low in sugar.

144
00:06:38,190 --> 00:06:38,950
It's quite sweet.

145
00:06:38,950 --> 00:06:40,270
Take some more.

146
00:06:40,750 --> 00:06:42,370
Try this.

147
00:06:44,310 --> 00:06:44,740
Here.

148
00:06:45,870 --> 00:06:46,730
Corn porridge?

149
00:06:47,420 --> 00:06:49,350
Corn juice. It's a drink.

150
00:06:49,420 --> 00:06:50,770
Come on. Try it.

151
00:06:53,070 --> 00:06:53,600
How is it?

152
00:06:54,420 --> 00:06:55,880
Isn't this corn porridge?

153
00:06:56,159 --> 00:06:57,040
Corn juice!

154
00:06:57,070 --> 00:06:58,570
It's a drink! A drink!

155
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,430
Okay. It's a drink.

156
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:03,860
Seriously.

157
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:06,080
You are quite something.

158
00:07:06,300 --> 00:07:07,760
You kept researching here

159
00:07:07,830 --> 00:07:09,270
and came up with corn juice.

160
00:07:09,270 --> 00:07:10,450
This is nothing.

161
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:14,020
It's just that, at home,

162
00:07:14,370 --> 00:07:16,800
we harvest so much corn every year.

163
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:18,370
I was thinking,

164
00:07:18,830 --> 00:07:20,500
if we can't sell them

165
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:22,150
or eat them all,

166
00:07:22,220 --> 00:07:23,360
isn't it a waste?

167
00:07:23,870 --> 00:07:24,810
It's a pity.

168
00:07:25,830 --> 00:07:26,920
While my wife

169
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:29,370
is waiting in line for her surgery,

170
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:31,700
I'll do some research on this.

171
00:07:32,220 --> 00:07:34,040
If yam juice can work,

172
00:07:34,130 --> 00:07:34,830
I believe

173
00:07:34,860 --> 00:07:35,980
my corn juice

174
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:38,500
can shine too.

175
00:07:39,830 --> 00:07:40,630
That's great.

176
00:07:42,070 --> 00:07:43,930
Zongbao, keep researching this.

177
00:07:44,330 --> 00:07:45,720
I've had no idea what to eat

178
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:47,330
these days anyway.

179
00:07:47,870 --> 00:07:48,570
Eat corn.

180
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:49,240
Right.

181
00:07:49,750 --> 00:07:51,010
You focus on the juice,

182
00:07:51,070 --> 00:07:52,330
and I focus on the food.

183
00:07:53,560 --> 00:07:54,360
This is great.

184
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:56,570
See? I don't even need to chew.

185
00:07:58,250 --> 00:07:58,680
What?

186
00:07:59,690 --> 00:08:01,370
Spit it out! Hurry!

187
00:08:03,060 --> 00:08:03,920
I swallowed it.

188
00:08:05,100 --> 00:08:06,270
Spit it out!

189
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:08,450
I swallowed it already.

190
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:13,710
This is what's left after I chewed it.

191
00:08:16,810 --> 00:08:19,140
You're not just keeping me from sleeping,

192
00:08:19,490 --> 00:08:20,990
you're trying to kill me.

193
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:25,110
It's fine.

194
00:08:25,180 --> 00:08:26,280
It's very clean.

195
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:29,310
You're always climbing up and down.

196
00:08:29,310 --> 00:08:30,510
What are you looking for? Let me help you.

197
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:31,770
Come. Come down first.

198
00:08:32,630 --> 00:08:33,820
Found it.

199
00:08:34,580 --> 00:08:35,380
Give me a hand.

200
00:08:41,299 --> 00:08:42,490
[The Late Love]

201
00:08:41,700 --> 00:08:44,230
Do you still recognize
your own handwriting?

202
00:08:45,050 --> 00:08:47,450
I'd recognize it
even if it turned to ashes.

203
00:08:48,530 --> 00:08:49,510
Did you call me over today

204
00:08:49,510 --> 00:08:50,980
because of The Late Love?

205
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:53,700
I told that stubborn mule long ago

206
00:08:54,150 --> 00:08:55,770
that the title wasn't good luck.

207
00:08:55,770 --> 00:08:57,000
The Late Love?

208
00:08:57,030 --> 00:08:58,430
He just wouldn't listen.

209
00:08:58,580 --> 00:08:59,620
Director,

210
00:08:59,650 --> 00:09:01,240
you always keep me guessing.

211
00:09:01,240 --> 00:09:02,940
Can you just be frank?

212
00:09:03,500 --> 00:09:06,390
The Late Love
is finally seeing a breakthrough.

213
00:09:08,670 --> 00:09:09,890
The studio agreed to make it?

214
00:09:09,890 --> 00:09:10,780
Not really.

215
00:09:11,390 --> 00:09:12,820
Your master won't change a single word.

216
00:09:12,820 --> 00:09:14,020
Why would they agree?

217
00:09:14,250 --> 00:09:15,890
Then what happened?

218
00:09:16,790 --> 00:09:18,520
A film studio from another city

219
00:09:18,870 --> 00:09:20,600
received the script you sent in

220
00:09:20,620 --> 00:09:22,150
and thought it was very good.

221
00:09:22,150 --> 00:09:24,080
Of course, they do have some notes,

222
00:09:24,290 --> 00:09:26,540
but overall they're positive about it.

223
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:28,840
A studio from another city?

224
00:09:28,970 --> 00:09:30,670
I never sent it out.

225
00:09:31,170 --> 00:09:32,710
Then someone must have

226
00:09:33,080 --> 00:09:34,700
done it for you.

227
00:09:41,010 --> 00:09:42,140
It's Zhuang Zhuang.

228
00:09:52,080 --> 00:09:55,050
My girlfriend is the best in the world!

229
00:09:57,890 --> 00:09:58,950
What are you doing?

230
00:09:59,130 --> 00:10:00,860
Someone has picked our script!

231
00:10:01,460 --> 00:10:02,380
Really?

232
00:10:03,700 --> 00:10:04,920
That's great!

233
00:10:05,010 --> 00:10:05,810
That's great!

234
00:10:07,010 --> 00:10:07,890
That's great!

235
00:10:09,390 --> 00:10:09,990
Thank you.

236
00:10:13,010 --> 00:10:13,500
I...

237
00:10:14,250 --> 00:10:15,870
I just felt the script was so good

238
00:10:15,870 --> 00:10:17,330
and shouldn't go to waste.

239
00:10:40,320 --> 00:10:41,510
Pick up your bag.

240
00:10:51,700 --> 00:10:52,560
Thank me again.

241
00:10:55,750 --> 00:10:58,200
Then... then I want to kiss you again.

242
00:11:02,340 --> 00:11:03,730
We're on the street.

243
00:11:05,250 --> 00:11:05,780
Alright.

244
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:07,390
From now on,

245
00:11:07,390 --> 00:11:08,200
if you miss me,

246
00:11:08,220 --> 00:11:09,550
you can page me anytime.

247
00:11:10,220 --> 00:11:11,080
Who'd miss you?

248
00:11:12,510 --> 00:11:13,490
Who'd miss me?

249
00:11:13,740 --> 00:11:14,530
You waited for me until this late,

250
00:11:14,530 --> 00:11:15,730
and you don't miss me?

251
00:11:16,520 --> 00:11:19,210
[Capital Film Studio]

252
00:11:16,960 --> 00:11:19,040
I called you here to tell you

253
00:11:19,250 --> 00:11:20,650
that the film studio said

254
00:11:20,800 --> 00:11:22,270
that with such a good script,

255
00:11:22,270 --> 00:11:24,600
they would invest a little no matter what.

256
00:11:24,750 --> 00:11:26,050
However,

257
00:11:27,530 --> 00:11:28,870
we still have to cover

258
00:11:29,100 --> 00:11:31,130
the bulk of the funding ourselves.

259
00:11:31,480 --> 00:11:32,610
Ourselves?

260
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:34,620
You know,

261
00:11:34,650 --> 00:11:36,320
everything's market-driven now.

262
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:38,200
Things aren't easy at the studio either.

263
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:40,260
How about this? Let's try all the ways

264
00:11:40,630 --> 00:11:42,840
and see if any

265
00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:44,380
private film companies

266
00:11:44,630 --> 00:11:45,130
or

267
00:11:45,150 --> 00:11:46,720
businessmen from other industries

268
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:47,980
are willing to invest.

269
00:11:49,720 --> 00:11:50,390
But Director Weng,

270
00:11:50,390 --> 00:11:52,050
I don't have any connections.

271
00:11:54,290 --> 00:11:55,500
Each film has its own destiny.

272
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:56,500
Take it as it comes

273
00:11:56,500 --> 00:11:57,430
and try our luck.

274
00:11:57,650 --> 00:11:59,180
I'll also try to ask around.

275
00:12:02,870 --> 00:12:03,960
Here is the situation.

276
00:12:03,960 --> 00:12:04,690
Well...

277
00:12:04,740 --> 00:12:07,150
the patient we had scheduled

278
00:12:07,250 --> 00:12:09,390
has a heart problem
found in pre-op checks,

279
00:12:09,390 --> 00:12:10,870
so the surgery can't be done.

280
00:12:10,870 --> 00:12:12,370
From the registrations,

281
00:12:12,700 --> 00:12:13,460
the best candidate now

282
00:12:13,460 --> 00:12:15,060
is your wife, Jiang Hongmei.

283
00:12:15,960 --> 00:12:18,270
She has post-lingual deafness,

284
00:12:18,370 --> 00:12:20,530
with relatively intact cochlear structure,

285
00:12:20,530 --> 00:12:21,700
making her the ideal candidate.

286
00:12:21,700 --> 00:12:22,770
If we delay

287
00:12:22,770 --> 00:12:23,460
too long,

288
00:12:23,460 --> 00:12:25,080
the surgery's effectiveness will decrease.

289
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:26,620
Okay, that's great.

290
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:28,820
Of course, this is a rare opportunity.

291
00:12:28,820 --> 00:12:30,460
If you decide to go ahead
with the surgery,

292
00:12:30,460 --> 00:12:32,390
get the patient admitted quickly.

293
00:12:33,650 --> 00:12:34,370
Great.

294
00:12:34,980 --> 00:12:36,840
My wife...

295
00:12:37,860 --> 00:12:39,050
is really lucky.

296
00:12:39,620 --> 00:12:41,510
But if she's admitted immediately,

297
00:12:41,510 --> 00:12:43,410
we need to pay right away, right?

298
00:12:43,890 --> 00:12:45,130
If you decide to do it,

299
00:12:45,170 --> 00:12:45,890
yes.

300
00:12:46,630 --> 00:12:47,890
As I told you last time,

301
00:12:48,050 --> 00:12:50,200
this is entirely self-funded—

302
00:12:50,350 --> 00:12:51,950
surgery, cochlear implant,

303
00:12:52,050 --> 00:12:53,240
and post-op rehab—

304
00:12:54,720 --> 00:12:55,390
financially,

305
00:12:55,390 --> 00:12:57,050
you need to be fully prepared.

306
00:12:57,670 --> 00:12:59,580
But can we delay it a bit?

307
00:13:00,170 --> 00:13:02,230
I haven't gathered enough money yet.

308
00:13:02,360 --> 00:13:03,940
Can I pay part of it first?

309
00:13:03,980 --> 00:13:04,840
Will that work?

310
00:13:05,670 --> 00:13:07,600
Then you'll have to queue up again.

311
00:13:07,750 --> 00:13:08,270
If

312
00:13:08,270 --> 00:13:10,220
more eligible patients come after,

313
00:13:10,220 --> 00:13:12,150
I can't say when it'll be your turn.

314
00:13:12,170 --> 00:13:12,770
I know.

315
00:13:13,890 --> 00:13:14,490
Of course,

316
00:13:14,700 --> 00:13:15,960
a surgery like this

317
00:13:15,960 --> 00:13:17,010
is indeed a heavy burden

318
00:13:17,010 --> 00:13:18,240
for a normal family,

319
00:13:18,820 --> 00:13:20,700
so you must think it through.

320
00:13:20,790 --> 00:13:21,450
Don't rush.

321
00:13:22,360 --> 00:13:23,300
We'll also

322
00:13:23,460 --> 00:13:24,120
get in touch

323
00:13:24,170 --> 00:13:26,010
with the next suitable patient.

324
00:13:26,290 --> 00:13:27,980
You can't do that.

325
00:13:28,750 --> 00:13:29,880
Don't contact them.

326
00:13:30,130 --> 00:13:31,910
I'll go borrow the money.

327
00:13:32,960 --> 00:13:35,790
It wasn't easy for my wife

328
00:13:35,820 --> 00:13:37,670
to wait for this surgery.

329
00:13:37,980 --> 00:13:39,290
I'll go borrow money.

330
00:13:40,290 --> 00:13:41,820
Can you wait a few more days?

331
00:13:44,220 --> 00:13:44,740
Alright.

332
00:13:44,740 --> 00:13:46,340
I'll let the department know

333
00:13:46,700 --> 00:13:47,580
and give you a few days.

334
00:13:47,580 --> 00:13:48,350
Okay.

335
00:13:48,460 --> 00:13:50,080
Thank you, then.

336
00:13:50,390 --> 00:13:51,100
-It's alright.
-Thank you.

337
00:13:51,100 --> 00:13:52,240
It's alright.

338
00:13:53,030 --> 00:13:54,230
I'll get going then.

339
00:13:54,340 --> 00:13:54,750
Okay.

340
00:13:55,620 --> 00:13:56,460
Hurry up then.

341
00:13:56,870 --> 00:13:57,580
Okay.

342
00:14:03,080 --> 00:14:04,580
Here's 820.

343
00:14:05,320 --> 00:14:07,130
I'll write you an IOU.

344
00:14:09,120 --> 00:14:10,130
No need. No need.

345
00:14:10,130 --> 00:14:11,340
There's no need for that.

346
00:14:11,340 --> 00:14:14,070
Come on. Even brothers
settle accounts clearly.

347
00:14:15,340 --> 00:14:17,160
I paid the tuition for my eldest
before the new year,

348
00:14:17,160 --> 00:14:18,890
so I only have this little bit left.

349
00:14:18,890 --> 00:14:20,500
Otherwise, I could give you more.

350
00:14:20,500 --> 00:14:21,240
Just use it for now.

351
00:14:21,240 --> 00:14:22,840
Why write an IOU?

352
00:14:22,420 --> 00:14:24,600
[I borrowed 820 yuan from Wang Qing today]

353
00:14:22,980 --> 00:14:23,840
We've known each other for so many years.

354
00:14:23,840 --> 00:14:25,040
If the villagers know

355
00:14:25,100 --> 00:14:25,960
that you wrote me an IOU,

356
00:14:25,960 --> 00:14:27,490
what would they think of us?

357
00:14:28,150 --> 00:14:28,790
Then write it.

358
00:14:28,790 --> 00:14:30,320
I'll just tear it up anyway.

359
00:14:30,510 --> 00:14:31,850
Stop messing around.

360
00:14:32,170 --> 00:14:32,570
You...

361
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:33,630
Just take it.

362
00:14:33,630 --> 00:14:35,560
If you give it to me, I'll tear it up.

363
00:14:36,320 --> 00:14:37,580
I'll tear it up anyway.

364
00:14:37,870 --> 00:14:38,750
Take it.

365
00:14:38,750 --> 00:14:39,370
Don't give it to me.

366
00:14:39,370 --> 00:14:39,770
You...

367
00:14:40,630 --> 00:14:42,820
Zongbao, let me say a few more words.

368
00:14:43,480 --> 00:14:44,670
Don't get mad, okay?

369
00:14:45,410 --> 00:14:45,860
What?

370
00:14:48,870 --> 00:14:50,800
We all know you're good to Hongmei.

371
00:14:51,270 --> 00:14:52,530
But some things are...

372
00:14:52,940 --> 00:14:55,080
are just out of our reach.

373
00:14:56,080 --> 00:14:56,720
We have to consider

374
00:14:56,720 --> 00:14:58,710
our own conditions.

375
00:15:03,320 --> 00:15:04,010
Thanks.

376
00:15:04,980 --> 00:15:07,050
I will definitely pay you back.

377
00:15:07,890 --> 00:15:08,290
You...

378
00:15:08,360 --> 00:15:08,960
Take it.

379
00:15:16,720 --> 00:15:17,450
I'm leaving.

380
00:15:17,740 --> 00:15:18,590
Take care.

381
00:15:18,740 --> 00:15:19,410
Thanks.

382
00:15:22,840 --> 00:15:26,940
Repairing range hoods!

383
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:31,010
Unclogging drains!

384
00:15:33,290 --> 00:15:37,130
Sharpening scissors

385
00:15:38,790 --> 00:15:42,740
and knives!

386
00:15:44,650 --> 00:15:45,340
Shengli, you're here.

387
00:15:45,340 --> 00:15:45,940
Zongbao.

388
00:15:46,740 --> 00:15:48,270
Here, your letter. Take it.

389
00:15:49,200 --> 00:15:49,930
What letter?

390
00:15:51,480 --> 00:15:52,360
Wait, this...

391
00:15:53,460 --> 00:15:54,630
This is money!

392
00:15:55,620 --> 00:15:56,500
This is just a little something

393
00:15:56,500 --> 00:15:57,620
from me and Zhuang Zhuang.

394
00:15:57,620 --> 00:15:58,600
Please take it.

395
00:15:59,320 --> 00:15:59,910
Come on.

396
00:16:01,050 --> 00:16:02,340
I can't accept this money.

397
00:16:02,340 --> 00:16:03,870
It's not easy for you to make money.

398
00:16:03,870 --> 00:16:04,320
Don't!

399
00:16:04,320 --> 00:16:05,820
You're not planning to pay it back,

400
00:16:05,820 --> 00:16:06,320
are you?

401
00:16:06,550 --> 00:16:08,010
We are lending this to you.

402
00:16:08,220 --> 00:16:08,750
Lending?

403
00:16:11,290 --> 00:16:11,750
Well...

404
00:16:12,980 --> 00:16:13,960
Thank you, then.

405
00:16:15,030 --> 00:16:16,030
I'll write you...

406
00:16:16,100 --> 00:16:17,410
an IOU.

407
00:16:18,360 --> 00:16:18,840
Okay.

408
00:16:18,890 --> 00:16:19,580
Sure.

409
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:20,550
Okay.

410
00:16:25,410 --> 00:16:25,810
You...

411
00:16:26,550 --> 00:16:27,530
Well, I...

412
00:16:28,740 --> 00:16:29,600
Shengli!

413
00:17:09,640 --> 00:17:10,089
Cao.

414
00:17:12,030 --> 00:17:13,130
What is this?

415
00:17:13,250 --> 00:17:13,780
Zongbao.

416
00:17:15,089 --> 00:17:16,099
About Mrs. Jiang,

417
00:17:16,230 --> 00:17:17,760
I've always wanted to help,

418
00:17:18,220 --> 00:17:19,619
but my means are limited.

419
00:17:19,829 --> 00:17:20,960
Anyway, just let me chip in.

420
00:17:20,960 --> 00:17:22,619
Please don't mind the amount.

421
00:17:23,960 --> 00:17:25,849
I'll write you an IOU.

422
00:17:25,940 --> 00:17:27,000
Come on, drop it.

423
00:17:27,030 --> 00:17:28,700
Stop talking. If you say more...

424
00:17:28,700 --> 00:17:29,630
I'm going to cry.

425
00:17:31,420 --> 00:17:32,150
Cao, you...

426
00:17:36,250 --> 00:17:37,290
Liang, you're back?

427
00:17:37,290 --> 00:17:37,880
Zongbao.

428
00:17:42,110 --> 00:17:43,270
This is all the ca-

429
00:17:43,350 --> 00:17:44,130
cash I have.

430
00:17:44,750 --> 00:17:46,410
It's just a token of my regard.

431
00:17:46,880 --> 00:17:47,480
Come on...

432
00:17:47,680 --> 00:17:49,140
Don't worry about it.

433
00:18:10,050 --> 00:18:10,580
Who is it?

434
00:18:13,720 --> 00:18:14,180
Mr. Guo?

435
00:18:18,350 --> 00:18:19,050
Ranran.

436
00:18:19,290 --> 00:18:20,290
Why are you here?

437
00:18:20,530 --> 00:18:22,090
No-nothing.

438
00:18:22,110 --> 00:18:24,490
I... I just need some fresh air.

439
00:18:24,830 --> 00:18:26,030
And you're drinking?

440
00:18:28,030 --> 00:18:29,080
Well, have...

441
00:18:29,180 --> 00:18:29,960
have a seat.

442
00:18:35,850 --> 00:18:37,980
Do you have something on your mind too?

443
00:18:38,940 --> 00:18:39,600
Have a seat.

444
00:18:52,380 --> 00:18:52,980
What's...

445
00:18:54,250 --> 00:18:55,610
bothering you?

446
00:18:55,790 --> 00:18:56,680
Tell me.

447
00:18:58,070 --> 00:19:00,160
Let me cheer you up.

448
00:19:05,250 --> 00:19:07,350
I came up to see the m—

449
00:19:09,940 --> 00:19:10,600
The moon...

450
00:19:11,720 --> 00:19:12,320
Here it is.

451
00:19:12,570 --> 00:19:14,340
It ran over there. Look.

452
00:19:16,230 --> 00:19:17,420
The moon today

453
00:19:17,610 --> 00:19:18,180
is so big

454
00:19:19,250 --> 00:19:20,050
and so bright.

455
00:19:21,810 --> 00:19:22,610
It's awesome.

456
00:19:24,180 --> 00:19:25,500
Seeing this moon

457
00:19:26,380 --> 00:19:29,940
reminds me of my wife and I.

458
00:19:31,810 --> 00:19:33,270
The night we got married,

459
00:19:33,980 --> 00:19:36,490
the moon was this big.

460
00:19:37,400 --> 00:19:38,260
It was amazing.

461
00:19:39,140 --> 00:19:40,340
I told her...

462
00:19:41,460 --> 00:19:42,240
I said,

463
00:19:43,160 --> 00:19:46,200
"Let's live a good life,

464
00:19:47,750 --> 00:19:49,150
and I'll take care of you.

465
00:19:52,070 --> 00:19:54,000
Even if you want the moon in the sky,

466
00:19:55,740 --> 00:19:57,090
I'll get it for you."

467
00:20:07,050 --> 00:20:08,440
When I was little,

468
00:20:09,510 --> 00:20:10,740
I also clamored every day

469
00:20:10,740 --> 00:20:12,470
for my dad to get the moon for me.

470
00:20:13,010 --> 00:20:13,980
Guess what?

471
00:20:14,940 --> 00:20:16,300
My dad placed

472
00:20:16,400 --> 00:20:18,260
a big basin of water in front of me.

473
00:20:18,380 --> 00:20:19,850
He said, "Look,

474
00:20:20,500 --> 00:20:20,980
isn't the moon

475
00:20:20,980 --> 00:20:22,110
right in the basin?"

476
00:20:24,380 --> 00:20:27,320
Then I tried to grab it,

477
00:20:27,590 --> 00:20:28,940
but caught nothing.

478
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:30,350
I told my dad,

479
00:20:31,070 --> 00:20:33,010
"Dad, you're a big liar.

480
00:20:33,250 --> 00:20:34,110
You lied to me."

481
00:20:35,460 --> 00:20:37,330
Your dad wasn't lying.

482
00:20:38,480 --> 00:20:40,180
At that time, your dad

483
00:20:40,270 --> 00:20:42,330
really wanted to get the moon for you.

484
00:20:42,940 --> 00:20:44,220
Fathers

485
00:20:44,830 --> 00:20:46,030
love their daughters

486
00:20:46,240 --> 00:20:47,740
so much.

487
00:20:51,980 --> 00:20:53,360
Your dad was smart.

488
00:20:54,640 --> 00:20:57,410
If my wife asked me for the moon,

489
00:20:57,570 --> 00:20:59,400
I wouldn't think of that trick.

490
00:21:06,450 --> 00:21:07,250
What's wrong?

491
00:21:08,480 --> 00:21:09,270
I miss my dad.

492
00:21:20,830 --> 00:21:21,640
It's so round.

493
00:21:24,920 --> 00:21:26,180
Mr. Guo, what's wrong?

494
00:21:27,010 --> 00:21:28,220
My wife and I...

495
00:21:31,020 --> 00:21:33,240
grew up together.

496
00:21:33,510 --> 00:21:34,680
In this life,

497
00:21:35,330 --> 00:21:36,630
I just want her

498
00:21:37,510 --> 00:21:39,310
to hear the birds singing again,

499
00:21:40,610 --> 00:21:42,140
hear me speak again,

500
00:21:43,920 --> 00:21:45,060
and hear me

501
00:21:45,500 --> 00:21:47,230
sing Henan opera for her again.

502
00:21:53,180 --> 00:21:53,840
Mr. Guo,

503
00:21:55,270 --> 00:21:57,070
haven't you saved enough money?

504
00:21:58,200 --> 00:21:58,750
They say

505
00:21:58,750 --> 00:22:01,830
a penny can stump a hero.

506
00:22:03,720 --> 00:22:05,110
I'm still short 60,000.

507
00:22:07,790 --> 00:22:09,120
I haven't saved enough,

508
00:22:10,070 --> 00:22:12,800
but the opportunity for the surgery
has arrived.

509
00:22:13,200 --> 00:22:14,090
Right now,

510
00:22:15,140 --> 00:22:16,350
I'm restless

511
00:22:17,530 --> 00:22:19,270
and don't know what to do.

512
00:22:23,440 --> 00:22:26,660
Mr. Guo, things will work out eventually.

513
00:22:27,790 --> 00:22:29,790
Eventually?

514
00:22:31,180 --> 00:22:34,900
The "eventually" is next week.

515
00:22:36,140 --> 00:22:37,610
But where is the way out?

516
00:22:38,590 --> 00:22:40,140
Where is the money?

517
00:22:40,830 --> 00:22:42,530
Let's bring her to Beijing

518
00:22:42,940 --> 00:22:44,800
and have her undergo the surgery.

519
00:22:46,850 --> 00:22:47,780
What did you say?

520
00:22:51,350 --> 00:22:52,750
Don't leave. Wait for me.

521
00:22:53,240 --> 00:22:53,880
Ranran.

522
00:22:55,420 --> 00:22:57,020
What were you talking about?

523
00:23:06,640 --> 00:23:09,100
Why did I tell a kid about this?

524
00:23:33,810 --> 00:23:34,350
Ranran.

525
00:23:35,430 --> 00:23:37,560
Mr. Guo, here.

526
00:23:36,090 --> 00:23:37,470
[Passbook Savings Account]

527
00:23:37,700 --> 00:23:38,200
Take it.

528
00:23:41,050 --> 00:23:41,660
Take it.

529
00:23:41,540 --> 00:23:42,440
[Passbook Savings Account]

530
00:23:42,640 --> 00:23:45,140
What are you doing?

531
00:23:46,160 --> 00:23:47,290
This is my pay

532
00:23:47,850 --> 00:23:49,050
and the money I saved.

533
00:23:49,510 --> 00:23:50,640
It should be enough.

534
00:23:55,880 --> 00:23:56,400
Ranran.

535
00:23:58,590 --> 00:24:01,740
This favor is too heavy.

536
00:24:04,330 --> 00:24:06,700
I can't accept it.

537
00:24:07,110 --> 00:24:09,630
Curing her is more important, Mr. Guo.

538
00:24:13,550 --> 00:24:14,110
Alright.

539
00:24:16,350 --> 00:24:17,080
I'll take it.

540
00:24:19,810 --> 00:24:21,470
I'll definitely pay you back.

541
00:24:22,670 --> 00:24:24,870
I don't need to use this money right now.

542
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:27,800
Let's get the moon for you first.

543
00:24:35,920 --> 00:24:36,660
Good girl.

544
00:24:52,530 --> 00:24:53,310
Good.

545
00:24:59,150 --> 00:24:59,790
Mr. Sui,

546
00:25:00,090 --> 00:25:02,460
did you read the script?

547
00:25:02,810 --> 00:25:03,940
Are you interested?

548
00:25:04,440 --> 00:25:05,030
I am.

549
00:25:06,330 --> 00:25:07,180
Great.

550
00:25:07,480 --> 00:25:08,880
Are we talking about art

551
00:25:09,440 --> 00:25:10,610
or business?

552
00:25:10,980 --> 00:25:12,810
Well... of course we...

553
00:25:13,660 --> 00:25:14,480
In business,

554
00:25:17,090 --> 00:25:18,440
spending money is making money.

555
00:25:18,440 --> 00:25:19,740
Exactly.

556
00:25:21,550 --> 00:25:22,140
Mr. Sui,

557
00:25:22,720 --> 00:25:24,590
since you want to be straightforward,

558
00:25:24,590 --> 00:25:25,890
let's speak frankly,

559
00:25:26,090 --> 00:25:26,720
okay?

560
00:25:26,880 --> 00:25:28,310
No movie

561
00:25:28,770 --> 00:25:30,550
would dare claim it's guaranteed

562
00:25:30,550 --> 00:25:32,210
to make money before release.

563
00:25:32,400 --> 00:25:34,110
But I can guarantee

564
00:25:34,440 --> 00:25:36,720
that the script is absolutely good.

565
00:25:37,400 --> 00:25:39,000
As long as the funds are in place,

566
00:25:39,000 --> 00:25:40,250
I can immediately gather

567
00:25:40,250 --> 00:25:41,260
the best actors

568
00:25:41,500 --> 00:25:43,070
and a good production team.

569
00:25:45,220 --> 00:25:46,080
Director Weng,

570
00:25:46,850 --> 00:25:48,250
your words

571
00:25:48,500 --> 00:25:49,180
make me feel

572
00:25:50,250 --> 00:25:52,380
that you are not only straightforward

573
00:25:52,550 --> 00:25:53,660
but also honest.

574
00:25:55,200 --> 00:25:56,610
If you patted your chest and said

575
00:25:56,610 --> 00:25:58,870
this movie would definitely make money,

576
00:25:58,940 --> 00:26:00,740
I would disappear immediately.

577
00:26:01,590 --> 00:26:03,030
In front of a straightforward person,

578
00:26:03,030 --> 00:26:04,350
I wouldn't dare not be straightforward,

579
00:26:04,350 --> 00:26:04,880
right?

580
00:26:05,140 --> 00:26:05,710
Right.

581
00:26:05,850 --> 00:26:07,310
I can invest in this movie.

582
00:26:08,270 --> 00:26:09,000
To me,

583
00:26:10,070 --> 00:26:11,010
it's pocket money.

584
00:26:11,010 --> 00:26:12,540
I can even fund it entirely.

585
00:26:12,880 --> 00:26:14,140
That's great, Mr. Sui.

586
00:26:14,500 --> 00:26:16,100
It took us a long time to write

587
00:26:16,160 --> 00:26:17,160
